          <p>Now, not all communication is a claim, because not all communication can be treated as something that could be true, right, correct, or could be false, wrong, incorrect. Take the sentence fragment: "going to the mall". This can't treated as a claim that could be true or could be false, because there is nothing to disagree about it. There is no subject that can be disagreed with. The fragment is also not making any judgements. If the sentence fragment was instead saying: "going to the mall is a good idea" then that would be an evaluable claim, that can therefore then be assumed true, or assumed false, to see which one of those implications holds up the best.</p>
        </div>
